        <p class="faq">
        What am I supposed to do with Five?
        </p>
        <p>
        You can rate salon professionals who helped you (hair stylists, barbers, manicurists, etc) or collect ratings from your clients.
        </br>
        </br>
        If you manage a salon, you can use Five to track customer satisfaction and evaluate talent.
        </p>
        </br>
        </br>

        <p class="faq">
        How does my salon become a Five member? 
        </p>    
        <p>
        Simply send us an email at <a href="mailto:newMember@fiveme.io?Subject=Get%20me%20on%20Five!">newMember@fiveme.io</a> and we'll take care of the rest.
        </br>
        </br>
        At Five we are hyper-aware of data integrity--we strive to show off and accurately represent your reputation. That's our mission and we take it very seriously.
        </br>
        </br>
        An automated web-based verification process is being built, but for now we will take care of this offline. 
        </p>
        </br>
        </br>
    <p class="faq">
         How do I, as an employee, become affiliated with a salon? 
        </p> 
        <p>
        When you sign up, you have an option to put in a <u>Business ID #</u> associated with your business, which you can get from your colleagues, a manager or request from <a href="mailto:newMember@fiveme.io?Subject=Get%20me%20on%20Five!">newMember@fiveme.io</a>
        </br>
        </br>
        You can also add or change this <u>Business ID #</u> at any time by editing your profile.
        </p>
